5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
6 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
8 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. As used in this section:
10 1. “Antisemitism” has the same meaning as provided for by the
11 International Holocaust Remembrance Alliance Working Definition of
12 Antisemitism, including its contemporary examples, as it was adopted
13 on May 26, 2016;
14 2. “Institution of higher education” means an institution of
15 higher education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
16 Education; and
17 3. “Public school” shall have the same meaning as provided for
18 in Section 1-106 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
19 B. Discrimination on the basis of race, ethnicity, national
20 origin, sex, disability, religion, or marital status against a
21 student or an employee in an institution of higher education or a
22 public school in this state shall be prohibited. No person in this
23 state shall, on the basis of race, ethnicity, national origin, sex,
24 disability, religion, or marital status, be excluded from
