1 part icipating in, be denied the benefits of, or be subjected to
2 discrimination under any institution of higher education or public
3 school program or activity or in any employment conditions or
4 practices conducted by an institution of higher education or a
5 public school that receives or benefits from federal or state
6 financial assistance.
7 C. The criteria for admission to a program or course at an
8 institution of higher education shall not have the effect of
9 restricting access by persons of a particular race, ethnicity,
10 national origin, sex, disability, religion, or marital status;
11 provided, this shall not infringe upon the rights of student faith-
12 based organizations and ethnic solidarity organizations to select
13 leadership committed to their group’s mission and principles.
14 D. All institution of higher education and public school
15 classes shall be available to all students without regard to race,
16 ethnicity, national origin, sex, disability, religion, or marital
17 status. Provided, however, the provisions of this subsection shall
18 not prohibit the provision of programs designed to meet the needs of
19 students with limited proficiency in English, gifted students, or
20 students with disabilities or programs tailored to students with
21 specialized talents or skills.
22 E. Guidance, counseling, and financial assistance services in
23 institutions of higher education and public schools shall be
24 available to all students equally and provided in the same manner
