1 or r esulting from institutional policies or programs on their
2 campuses motivated by or including antisemitic intent in an
3 identical manner to discrimination motivated by race.
4 C. All institutions of higher education and public schools are
5 encouraged to:
6 1. Incorporate antisemitism awareness training for all
7 students, faculty, administrators, and campus police;
8 2. Integrate Jewish American heritage curriculum for students
9 that incorporates Jewish experiences in the United States of America
10 pre- and post-revolution, pre- and post-World War II and the
11 Holocaust, and in modern times; and
12 3. Place reasonable time, place, and manner restrictions on
13 speech to ensure order and protect the rights of all students.
14 D. 1. The State Department of Education shall designate a
15 Title VI coordinator dedicated to monitoring antisemitic
16 discrimination and harassment in public schools in this state. All
17 public schools shall electronically report incidents and complaints
18 of antisemitic discrimination and harassment to the Title VI
19 coordinator. The Title VI Coordinator shall establish, maintain,
20 and publicize a formal reporting process whereby students, parents,
21 staff, and faculty can submit complaints of antisemitic
22 discrimination and harassment.
23 2. The Title VI coordinator designated pursuant to paragraph 1
24 of this subsection shall thoroughly investigate all submitted
